Project Description:
Three rule of law projects providing technical assistance to support the Albanian police to:
- carry out proper forensic investigation of crime scenes; 
- promote  the principles of the Open Government Partnership through the deployment of UK expertise;
- Improve the efficiency of the UK-Albania Prisoner Transfer Agreement.

To help the Government of Serbia improve its transparency by developing digital communications expertise and a digital communication strategy for the public sector in Serbia by: 
- sharing UK expertise through tutorials and workshops for the Serbian civil service communicators; 
- producing Guidelines For The Use Of Social Media And Digital Communication for Serbian Governmental Institutions; 
- developing and enhancing digital capacities in key government ministries.

Through a number of complementary components, the project’s aim is to strengthen the capacity of Serbia's new Office for the CPE, to enable it to: 
- take landmark cases to court, to establish strategic precedents to promote beneficial changes to the relevant laws, policies and procedures at a local and national level;
- design comprehensive anti-discrimination campaigns that educate and motivate the government and the public to oppose discrimination; 
- join forces with NGOs in order to increase anti-discrimination advocacy in Serbia.

Promoting the rule of law by helping the judicial system and the advocacy profession in Albania to meet international required standards through: 

- delivery of legal education; 

- improving the entrance examination to the Magistrates School to ensure the best quality legal professionals enter the Albanian judicial system;

- assistance towards the implementation of the Albanian Justice Sector Strategy.
